        "subject": "LU-1158 general: support for nanosecond m/a/ctimes in Lustre",
        "message": "LU-1158 general: support for nanosecond m/a/ctimes in Lustre\n\nExtra fields were added in various structures (mostly ones sent over\nwire, e.g. mdt_body) for passing around nanosecond m/a/ctimes. Since\nldiskfs/ext4 and the Linux kernel already supported nanosecond\ntimestamps, it was only a matter of filling in and copying the new\nfields in on-wire structures with nanosecond times the rest of the\nsystem provided. Superblocks in the Linux VFS for Lustre also had to\nhave their s_time_gran fields modified as well to reflect the new time\ngranularity, and a new OBD connect flag has been added to reflect\nsupport for nanosecond timestamps. Finally, the 39X series of tests in\nsanity.sh have been modified to check nanosecond time coherency as\nwell.\n\nOne crucial point to note is that the ost_lvb structure had to be\nmodified in order to pass along nanosecond times, which required\nincreasing its size. Since the LVB is apparently not too friendly to\nsuch changes, it is possible (likely?) that this patch will break\ncompatability with previous versions of Lustre without the addition of\nanother patch to support variable LVB sizes.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Isami Romanowski <isami@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ie392d153ae213330dfff6e14bfa2c568959a8ff1\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
